<h4>Instructions for uploading directly from mobile device (iphone)</h4>
	<ol>
		<li>Download the OneTouch app and begin using it. You can enter blood sugars manually or upload them directly to your phone via bluetooth using certain OneTouch meters like the OneTouch Verio Flex.</li>
		<li>Be sure you have the Google Drive or Dropbox app on your smartphone. You'll need it to upload directly to this site with your phone.</li>
		<li>Open the OneTouch app and click the top-right button on the top right to export data.<br/><img src="1.PNG" height=334 width=188></li>
		<li>Select CSV <br/><img src="2.PNG" height=334 width=188></li>
		<li>Select the maximum days as your timeframe (don't worry, the system won't allow duplicates), and click the "open in" button </br><img src="3.PNG" height=334 width=188></li>						
		<li>Find the button that says "Copy to Dropbox" (or Google Drive) and click that. You need dropbox or drive installed on your phone. </br><img src="4.PNG" height=334 width=188></li>
		<li>Once the data is saved, go back to this site and select to Choose File...</li>
		<li>On iphone, you should see a screen that looks like this, select Dropbox </br><img src="6.PNG" height=334 width=188></li>
		<li>Click to Import CSV</li>
	</ol>
